This armor is white plastoid-composite body armor over a sealed black body glove. In this respect it appears similar to the armor worn by their predecessors of the Clone Wars. The complete ensemble encases the body, and typically has no individually distinguishing marking outside of rank, so much so that casual first-time observers would sometimes mistake the stormtroopers for some form of battle droids.

The armor also protects the troopers from very harsh environments as well as projectiles and impact weapons. The armor might be penetrated by a direct blaster bolt, but would significantly reduce damage from the absorbed bolt. Blast energy sinks were distributed around the armor to absorb energy from a blaster bolt. The insulated body glove allowed for comfortable operations in an very wide range of climates, including even total vacuum conditions, or immense extremes of cold and heat. In this respect, it could be argued that the armor is much less suited to battle than it's clone armor predecessor, and much more suitable as a high-tech survival suit.

There are a variety of different kinds of armor intended to defend against the harsh enviroments of space, deflect the impact of blaster bolts and protect versus all types of damage that can be found on a battlefield. These suits are usually built in with a personal shield generator.

The E-11 blaster rifle is a blaster rifle manufactured by BlasTech Industries during the Galactic Civil War. It is the standard blaster rifle of the Imperial stormtroopers. A powerful, light and compact weapon, the E-11 is used widely through the galaxy.

A blaster is a ranged weapon that fires bursts of particle beam energy called blaster bolts from a replaceable power cell. The most commonly used weapon in the Galaxy, blasters' intense beams consisting of compacted high-energy particles and intense light can kill or paralyze their target, depending on their setting.

Power paks or power cells provide energy for many vehicles, and small blaster weapons. Most power cells contain concentrated amounts of gases that, when heated, form plasma. In small blasters, power cells are used to create blaster bolts that are not nearly as powerful as blasters using a combination of magazines containing gases (that after being heated would change into plasma) and proper Blaster power packs. A small power cell could be used to power a prosthetic without the need for recharging.

This holdout blaster pistol, sometimes known as a scout blaster, is a standard-issue weapon used by the scout troopers of the Galactic Empire. Clone scout troopers of the 41st Elite Legion were also known to carry these weapons during the latter stages of the Clone Wars.

This compact, one-handed blaster is fitted with a side-mounted targeting scope and phase amplifier, and featured a miniature gas cell on the rear. The weapon had a short-range barrel. Scout troopers commonly carry these weapons in a boot holster. Because scout troopers wore padded gloves, the pistol has a pressure-sensitive stock rather than a trigger. The trooper is able to grip the stock with two gloved fingers through the enlarged finger guard.

Bacta is a synthetic chemical substance that consists of gelatinous, translucent red alazhi and kavam bacterial particles that are mixed within a colorless, viscous fluid known as ambori. When a patient is exposed to bacta, the bacterial particles within seek out wounds and promote rapid tissue regeneration while preventing the emergence of scar tissue. Bacta is often thought of as a "miracle fluid" and seems to be effective against almost every type of injury and ailment across an incredible cross-section of species throughout the Galaxy.

Kolto is a liquid known for it's healing abilities. It is found in the water oceanic planet Manaan, with a significant concentration near the Hrakert Rift along with other underwater chasms. It is considered a valuable commodity during the Jedi Civil War, but it's significance was lost over time, being replaced in favor of bacta.

Not as effective as Bacta for wounds, it is used by soldiers in the battlefield to clean themselves of infections and impurities.

The more used on them, the more it will sap from their strength. The only way to return to perfect health is to soak in a Bacta Tank.

A personal energy shield is defensive technology that projects a field of energy that protects the user from blaster fire, the elements, or other hazards. Most are small enough to be worn on a belt or arm. When activated, the device protects the wearer with a glowing energy field. Typically, the standard energy shield was only effective against energy attacks, such as blaster bolts.
An armguard is a small protective shield that can be attached with ease to the forearm of a soldier. It is useful for deflecting blaster shots or blades.

Deflector shields, also known simply as shields, are translucent or transparent energy fields produced by deflector shield generators. These generators are usually placed on planets, droids, starships, space stations or individual buildings. The primary purpose of the shield is to block or deflect projectiles and lasers from hitting the object under protection.

Stealth field generators are special types of belts that are portable, personal cloaking devices. They make their users all but invisible at medium and long ranges, however, a clumsy user could be easily detected at close quarters.
Iridonian field boots are sturdy footwear often favored by the Zabraks of Iridonia. Even the Jedi Master Agen Kolar prefers to wear Iridonian field boots.
Ubese boots are footwear that the Ubese use in conjunction with their armor. They are padded and tight, and provide protection against attacks aimed at the lower legs.

Technican Bracers have a built in computer database that allows the user to access a network of information on a variety of topics, including different species, planets and can be used to tap into computers.
This cloak provides a dark shadow for the wearer to hide beneath and avoid detection.
Modeled after the Eriadu Strength Amplifier, these Power Gloves use bursts of repulsorlift energy to assist movement, effectively giving the user tremendous strength.

The Stun Gauntlet is a heavy-duty glove that delivers an electric shock upon impact. Due to circuitry interwoven throughout the stun gauntlet, electricity is transferred from the energy cells to the impact point and causes the weapon to glow with electrical energy when activated. One of the known manufacturers of stun gauntlets is Palandrix, which claims to have made a stun gauntlet variety for virtually all known sentient species.

Infiltrator Gloves are equipped with an advanced A.I. unit that the wearer can use to tap into nearby security or computer systems through cables or wireless transmission. The system also stabilizes the wearer's hands for detail work, increasing their dexterity.

Ryyk Blades are simple traditional swords constructed by the Wookiees of Kashyyyk. The design of these weapons vary greatly between individuals, but all Ryyk Blades are hand-constructed and are considered an extension of the wielder, much like the Wookiee relationship with their Bowcasters. The average weight of a Ryyk was around fifteen kilograms, but Wookiees could wield them with surprising speed and grace. 

The blade was first developed when the Wookiees were still technologically primitive; they were used for clearing paths through the thick forests of Kashyyyk and fending off vicious predators. Ryyk blades were used heavily by Trandoshan slavers during the Clone Wars and currently, by Wookiee Berserkers during the Galactic Civil War.

A stun baton is a nonlethal short-range melee weapon that immobilizes organic targets with a powerful electrical shock. It requires the user to physically touch the target in order to immobilize them effectively.

Vibroweapons are a family of weapons that utilize high-speed sonic vibrations to turn a regular object into a deadly weapon; most commonly found on swords, vibrogenerators can also be found on axes, pikes, knives, etc. Almost anything with a blade has the potential to be turned into a vibroweapon.

The tip of the Force Pike is a vibro-edged head with a stun module that could knock a full-grown Wookiee unconscious using a concentrated nerve impulse similar to that featured in the stun setting of a blaster rifle. The impulse works by overloading the central nervous system, effectively knocking the victim unconscious. When the vibro-edge is set to maximum it could rip through steel bulkheads and easily dismember most organic beings. The control settings and power generator are located at the pike's grip. It should be noted that Force Pikes are not related to the Force.

The BlasTech DL-18 blaster pistol is a cheap weapon commonly and currently in use, in the Galatic Civil War.

Weapons of this make are common on Tatooine (several of Jabba the Hutt's skiff guards use DL-18 pistols), especially in the infamously violent city of Mos Eisley; hence, the model is sometimes nicknamed the "Mos Eisley Special".

A blaster is a ranged weapon that fires bursts of particle beam energy called blaster bolts from a replaceable power cell. The most commonly used weapon in the Galaxy, blasters' intense beams consisting of compacted high-energy particles and intense light can kill or paralyze their target, depending on their setting.

The Czerka 84-U hunting rifle is a weapon produced by Czerka Arms.

Wam Lufba found this rifle when he was thrown into the rancor pit in Jabba's Palace. He used it to escape certain death.

The gaderffii, or gaffi stick, is the traditional melee weapon of the Tusken Raiders of Tatooine. Crafted out of whatever salvage is at hand, they are very effective in close combat. Nearly every Tusken is proficient in the use of these weapons and more Tuskens chose the gaffi over the Tusken Cycler.

Kolto is a liquid known for it's healing abilities. It is found in the water oceanic planet Manaan, with a significant concentration near the Hrakert Rift along with other underwater chasms. It is considered a valuable commodity during the Jedi Civil War, but it's significance was lost over time, being replaced in favor of bacta.

Not as effective as Bacta for wounds, it is used by soldiers in the battlefield to clean themselves of infections and impurities.

Bacta is a synthetic chemical substance that consists of gelatinous, translucent red alazhi and kavam bacterial particles that are mixed within a colorless, viscous fluid known as ambori. When a patient is exposed to bacta, the bacterial particles within seek out wounds and promote rapid tissue regeneration while preventing the emergence of scar tissue. Bacta is often thought of as a "miracle fluid" and seems to be effective against almost every type of injury and ailment across an incredible cross-section of species throughout the Galaxy.

The gem set in the center of this amulet is no average crystal, instead it is a device designed to emit a portable shield of protection around the user and attempts to deflect damage away.

Implants are a technological marvel, tiny devices that are placed into the body of the owner and provide increases to their attributes with small drawbacks. Research on the long-term effects of using implants show only a minor chance of serious health defects and that risk is increased with the amount implanted in the host. It is a strictly up-held medical requirement that only two implants be worn at a time.

Bandoliers, were medium to large items of utilitarian clothing that the owner could wear around their left or right shoulder down across their torso, or as a large belt. Normally worn by military or paramilitary forces as well as mercenaries and others who needed large supplies of ammunition, bandoliers consisted of many ammunition pouches sewn together or snapped to a belt. Though typically used to carry extra ammunition for blaster-type and other ranged weaponry, bandoliers could also carry grenades, supplies of synthrope, and other sorts of items useful on the battlefield or in covert operations.

Within this syringe is enough adrenaline to rescue someone from the brink of death. However, the revival is only meant to be temporary and the person revived will feel drained. The more used on them, the more it will sap from their strength. The only way to return to perfect health is to soak in a Bacta Tank.

Fragmentation grenades are very basic. They explode when thrown, showering the enemy in shrapnel. It's not elegant, but it's definitely effective.
Smoke grenades release a thick cloud of smoke, obscurring the vision and causing disorientation to all caught in the effect..
